Q1: What is the highest mountain in the world, and where is it located?
The highest mountain in the world is Mount Everest, located on the border between Nepal and China in the Himalayas.

Q2: Which mountain has the second-highest peak after Mount Everest, and where is it located?
K2, located on the border between Pakistan and China in the Karakoram range, has the second-highest peak.

Q3: Which mountain in Tanzania is the highest in Africa?
Mount Kilimanjaro, located in Tanzania, is the highest mountain in Africa.

Q4: In which range is Denali, also known as Mount McKinley, located?
Denali (Mount McKinley) is located in the Alaska Range.

Q5: What is the range of Mount Blanc?
Mount Blanc is part of the Alps range, shared between France and Italy.

Q6: Which mountain in Argentina is the highest outside of Asia?
Aconcagua, located in Argentina, is the highest mountain outside of Asia.

Q7: Which mountains have been climbed since ancient times?
Mount Olympus in Greece and Mount Fuji in Japan have records of ascents from ancient times.

Q8: Where can you find Mount Ararat?
Mount Ararat is located in Turkey within the Ararat Massif.

Q9: Which mountain has cultural significance rather than a recorded first ascent year?
Mauna Kea in Hawaii, USA, has cultural significance rather than a documented first ascent year.

Q10: Which mountain is located in the Troodos Mountains of Cyprus?
Mount Olympus is located in the Troodos Mountains of Cyprus.
